        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare hereditary immune deficiency with skin involvement characterized by early-onset cold urticaria after generalized exposure to cold air or evaporative cooling and not after contact with cold objects. Additional immunologic abnormalities are often present - antibody deficiency recurrent infections autoimmune disease and symptomatic allergic disease."
